<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="430" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4001/13.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Snyder</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Holland
                                        Bay, Jamaica</hi></placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-22"><hi rend="italic">January 22,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Estimate 1,500 instantly killed; about 900 buried; others burned where
                            found; many injured dead since; after inquiry learn no Americans
                            identified dead or injured. Kingston Hotel not yet cleared; Americans
                            presumed buried there. Approximate total deaths 1,800. No scarcity food.
                            Medicines, disinfectants urgently needed. Water supply fair. Thirty
                            thousand reported homeless. Clearing streets of debris rapidly pursued.
                            People tranquil.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Snyder.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>